<br>
As I see it there quite a few advantages for closed bids:<br>
<br>
1. It is much much faster to implement. Of all those voting, how many of you have actually had to handle the bidding? How much longer do you think it will take when people can keep on incrementing their bids until they run out of RP? <br>
<br>
2. Open bidding can lead to aggravation, people pumping up prices and all sort of other related issues where one person is constantly having to raise their bid due to someone else, and then perhaps trying to get revenge later.<br>
<br>
3. As people get more points bids may keep escalating more and more out of control.<br>
<br>
4. If someone is keen to get an item, with a closed bid they can make an initial high bid and the whole thing is over and done quickly. It stops people messing about trying to get items for the least amount of points they possibly can. Those who really want an item, get it. <br>
<br>
5. With open bidding extemely valuable items may be obtained for just 1RP, just because they are lucky and nobody else on the raid qualified to loot it. With closed bidding they are more likely to bid a realistic amount, unless they are closely aware of how many others want.<br>
<br>
6. Open bidding severely discriminates against classes that are then in large numbers - e.g.  in Kael we had 2 chain users and about 12 silk users. With open bidding the 2 chain users could get almost every item for 2RP where the silk users might be outbidding each other and paying significantly more.<br>
<br>
My strongest objection is to the time and effort taken to sort out loot with open bids. I was asked to stop the pulls as it was, just so we could sort out loot. I chose not to, I wanted to keep everyone busy and get more drops <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  With open bidding, that might become necessary. It probably takes a few minutes for every drop with open bidding, we had about 10 drops, so that's about half an hour of a 4 hour raid wasted.<br>
<br>
So please, think twice about this. Don't just vote for open bidding because that way you'll get loot for the minimum number of points you can. Think about the people organising the raid and the looting. Think about the time taken, the effort and stress involved.<br>
<br>
Vote for closed bidding! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/bscarab5467.showUserPublicProfile?gid=runemoon>Runemoon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/3/02 4:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fscarab5467frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Open or hidden bidding during loot auctions?</span><hr size=1> An honest opinion, from an honest Cleric.<br>
