<br>
I still think the advantages of closed bidding vs open far outweigh the disadvantages. However, given that not everyone feels the same way, perhaps we should just let the raid leaders choose? They can announce open or closed bidding in the signup, so anyone not happy doesn't have to come along. Then after a while, perhaps it will become clearer which system works best and we can look at making one the official standard.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/bscarab5467.showUserPublicProfile?gid=runemoon>Runemoon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(12/5/02 4:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fscarab5467frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Open or hidden bidding during loot auctions?</span><hr size=1> Valid points, Goldark.<br>
